## 📌 Project Overview

The Library Management System is a SQL-based database project designed to manage library operations efficiently. This project demonstrates database design, CRUD operations, data analysis, stored procedures, and business reporting using SQL.

The database tracks:

- Books and Categories
- Library Members
- Employees and Branches
- Book Issue & Return Transactions
- Rental Revenue
- Branch Performance

The project showcases practical SQL skills used in real-world database management and analytics roles.

---
## Database Schema

![ERD Diagram](ERD/erd.png)

---

## 🎯 Business Objectives

- Manage library inventory and book availability.
- Track book issuance and returns.
- Monitor member activity.
- Generate revenue and branch performance reports.
- Identify overdue books and calculate penalties.
- Automate book issue and return processes using Stored Procedures.

---

## 🗂️ Database Schema

The system consists of the following tables:

| Table | Description |
|---------|-------------|
| Branch | Library branch information |
| Employees | Staff details and branch assignments |
| Members | Registered library members |
| Books | Book inventory and availability |
| Issued_Status | Book issue transactions |
| Return_Status | Book return transactions |

### Entity Relationships

- One Branch → Many Employees
- One Member → Many Book Issues
- One Book → Multiple Issue Transactions
- One Issue Record → One Return Record

